The paper deals with capacity regions of multiple access channels with state information known strictly causally to the encoders. This falls under the information theory (cs.IT) sub-category. The paper also discusses examples and variations, which could potentially fall under multimedia (cs.MM) or signal processing (cs.SI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves the use of algorithms and protocols, which could fall under networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses theoretical bounds and proofs, which could fall under the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
